<main role="main" class="container-fluid"><div class="section">
		<img class="section-pic" src="media/square/img2.jpg">
		<div>
			<p class="section-article">Let me start off by saying labor & delivery does NOT have to be scary and can be an amazing experience. The thoughts you fix your mind on make a difference.
			So here we go
			April 15th at 5:30am I woke up to what I knew was my baby “dropping”, I literally heard his head hit my pelvis. I figured in the next day or two he would come. WELL ... 6:20am I had my first contraction.. and from that moment on they were 4 minutes apart. I didn’t mention it to Josh because I was told they’d start out random and far apart so he went to work. About an hour into 4 minute apart contractions I texted Josh and told him “We’re gonna have a baby today.. you need to come home”.
			I basically started out in active labor and ended up laboring at home for 3 hours. Midwives and doula told us it was time, so once Josh had the car packed, we headed to the hospital!
			I labored 3 hours at the hospital, moving all around (thankful for intermittent monitoring!!). Water broke about an hour or so in & I immediately felt the need to push but it was too soon (7cm). My Doula said I transitioned in the shower (OUCH).
			Once I was at 10cm, my eyes were closed the whole time haha.. I was in the zone. As I gripped his hand as hard as I could, I just heard Josh telling me to give it all I had... that I was so close. I honestly couldn’t have done it without his encouragement. He was and is the BEST husband and dad.
			I pushed for about 15-20 minutes and Joshua Samuel joined us at 12:21
			6 hours of labor naturally with no tearing, just like I prayed for OKAY GOD.
			That day goes down in the books for the most rewarding, joyful & exciting day of my life. I’m honestly still trying to find words for it. BUT the truth is, no matter what your story is, birthing your baby is to be celebrated and I hope you feel empowered to do ANYTHING.
			My hope in sharing this is that it encourages you pregnant mommas ... your body was made for this!</p>
